{"id":40,"date":"2025-03-27T11:07:49","date_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:07:49","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/?p=40"},"modified":"2025-03-27T11:08:27","modified_gmt":"2025-03-27T11:08:27","slug":"decadent-chocolate-lava-cake","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/2025\/03\/27\/decadent-chocolate-lava-cake\/","title":{"rendered":"Decadent Chocolate Lava Cake"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>This indulgent dessert features a gooey molten chocolate center, perfect for chocolate lovers.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Ingredients<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>\u00bd cup (1 stick) unsalted butter<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>4 oz dark chocolate (60\u201370% cocoa)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 large eggs<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>2 large egg yolks<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bc cup granulated sugar<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>1 tsp vanilla extract<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bc cup all-purpose flour<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>\u00bd tsp salt<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Butter and cocoa powder (for greasing ramekins)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Powdered sugar (for garnish)<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vanilla ice cream or whipped cream (optional)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Instructions<\/strong><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 1: Preparing the Ramekins<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Preheat oven to 425\u00b0F (220\u00b0C).<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Grease four 6-ounce ramekins with butter and dust with cocoa powder. This prevents sticking.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 2: Melting the Chocolate and Butter<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In a heatproof bowl, melt the butter and chocolate over a double boiler or in the microwave (in 30-second intervals).<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stir until smooth and let cool slightly.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 3: Making the Batter<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>In another bowl, whisk eggs, egg yolks, sugar, and vanilla until light and fluffy.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gradually add melted chocolate, stirring constantly.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sift in flour and salt, folding gently until combined.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 4: Baking the Lava Cakes<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Divide the batter evenly among the prepared ramekins.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bake for 10\u201312 minutes, until the edges are firm but the center is still soft.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Let the cakes rest for 1 minute before inverting onto plates.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Step 5: Serving<\/strong><\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Dust with powdered sugar.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>This indulgent dessert features a gooey molten chocolate center, perfect for chocolate lovers. Ingredients Instructions Step 1: Preparing the Ramekins Step 2: Melting the Chocolate [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":41,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[4],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-40","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-desserts"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/40","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=40"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/fastmealideas.store\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/40\/r